main event: A single black bell-shaped object with erratic flight, tilting, hovering with no visible attachment was observed by a civilian in a car driving east of Naval Air Station Cecil Field, Florida.
interesting points: The object had a speed range of 8 to 9, and the observer pursued it at speeds up to 90 mph.
The observer's car stopped when the object hovered over the highway, approximately 15 feet above the ground and in close proximity to the observer.
The object was described as similar to the 'Adamski's Saucers'.
The observer requested no publicity and anonymously reported the matter to the local press.
When an unassociated jet aircraft took off from NAS Cecil Field, the object departed at almost instantaneous high velocity.
location: 1 to 8 miles east of NAS Cecil Field, Florida
